&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with software engineers, mechanical engineers, and other team members to integrate hardware with software and mechanical designs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct tests and simulations to ensure the functionality and reliability of hardware systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve hardware issues and provide technical support during the product development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare documentation for hardware designs, specifications, and test procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS, MS or higher degree in Mechanical engineering or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in hardware design and prototyping, including both electrical and mechanical components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CAD software for mechanical design (Solidworks, Onshape, or other).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Arduino or similar platforms for electronic prototyping and control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with 3D printing and rapid prototyping techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of electronic components, circuit design, and signal processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with testing and debugging hardware systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with robotics, teleoperation, or digital twin systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with human-centered considerations for robot design&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with actuator and sensor design for high performance haptic devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with high-speed control systems, including low-level firmware&lt;/li&gt;
