&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Skild AI, we are building the world&#39;s first general purpose robotic intelligence that is robust and adapts to unseen scenarios without failing. We believe massive scale through data-driven machine learning is the key to unlocking these capabilities for the widespread deployment of robots within society. Our team consists of individuals with varying levels of experience and backgrounds, from new graduates to domain experts. Relevant industry experience is important, but ultimately less so than your demonstrated abilities and attitude. We are looking for passionate individuals who are eager to explore uncharted waters and contribute to our innovative projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Mechatronics Technician to join our team to develop the systems and processes that ensure quality, reliability, and performance across our robotics and autonomous platforms. This role will involve working hands-on with aerial, ground, and integrated hardware systems—building prototypes, fabricating test setups, and supporting manufacturing workflows. You’ll collaborate closely with Electrical, Mechanical, and Firmware Engineers to accelerate prototyping, improve reliability, and lay the foundation for scalable production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1536&quot; data-end=&quot;1630&quot;&gt;Build and test prototypes, sub-assemblies, and feasibility units under engineering guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1633&quot; data-end=&quot;1760&quot;&gt;Interpret schematics, diagrams, and layouts to perform testing, checkout, troubleshooting, and rework of PCBAs and harnesses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1763&quot; data-end=&quot;1860&quot;&gt;Fabricate custom test equipment, boxes, and harnesses; procure and source components as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1863&quot; data-end=&quot;1998&quot;&gt;Operate and set up standard test equipment (oscilloscopes, analyzers, supplies, DMMs) and perform PCBA/cable rework to IPC standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2001&quot; data-end=&quot;2071&quot;&gt;Adapt plans quickly in a fast-paced environment with evolving goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2104&quot; data-end=&quot;2190&quot;&gt;3+ years’ experience as an engineering technician in a prototype or development lab.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2193&quot; data-end=&quot;2295&quot;&gt;Strong ability to read/interpret PCBA schematics, cable drawings, and test procedures independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2298&quot; data-end=&quot;2406&quot;&gt;Experience with prototype electro-mechanical hardware (PCBAs, cables, harnesses, robotic/vehicle systems).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2409&quot; data-end=&quot;2568&quot;&gt;Hands-on skills: soldering, crimping, rework, cable assembly to IPC standards; familiarity with electrical components, connectors, tools, and test equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2571&quot; data-end=&quot;2632&quot;&gt;Solid grasp of fundamental electrical engineering concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Base Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$70,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$150,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

